    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello @ricktbaker,\n\nThe goal of instantsearch.js was to provide a unified set of widgets that share the same 'state' (filters applied, query typed, etc).\n\nIf you want to remove all the current filters through the UI, you can have a look at the [clearAll](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#clearall) widget.\n\nIf you want to do it programmatically, you can have access to the `.helper` property of your instantsearch instance, which is an instance of https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js. You can then [clear filters](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js#clearing-filters) from here.\n\nI would suggest the first solution, as it is more in line with the underlying philosophy of the instantsearch.js project. The other one might work but is a bit hackish.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-12-22T10:26:38Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/750#issuecomment-166576219",
